<paragraph id="2D31C1D3EA20343991267C6EFF23E803" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName id="5AE17DCCA5235C07F82CA365CA3DA929" LSID="666B05B5-C5E8-5E3B-8C20-3C32A9B2E128" authority="(Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382 (1926)." authorityName="Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">Melanconis marginalis (Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382 (1926).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CE2928C7A5414DA724BE42D84C3A9113" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B86CA1D2238EC9126DBC7DB999E44CE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="443FA0F263168188F2A96D8E9E6C8582" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
This species is here subdivided into four subspecies below. See under subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="4B1D60D747D0333C9DB62E2010E57CCE" authorityName="subsp. marginalis (Peck) Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="subsp. marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="subSpecies" species="marginalis" subSpecies="marginalis">marginalis</taxonomicName>
for the original species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC646BB6E73263D7E0292891621854FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">
Although 
<bibRefCitation id="DEDBC919B4F8309E12B73F3260A75730" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="Papers from the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="377 - 396" refId="B62" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1926a. Cultural life-histories of Diaporthe. I. Papers from the Michigan Academy of Science, Arts and Letters 6: 377 - 396" title="Cultural life-histories of Diaporthe. I." volume="6" year="1926 a">Wehmeyer (1926a)</bibRefCitation>
combined 
<taxonomicName id="27934132E7A2C7A52DDC598EE747075A" authorityName="Peck" authorityYear="1887" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="A5132100B8A61AF2A1EF68E1C8F74CAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Diaporthe marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="744A9B7C08F6BDCDA8BA6AD91E0F2C95" authorityName="Tul. &amp; C. Tul., Select. fung. carpol. (Paris) 2: 115" authorityYear="1863" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E1BE3AB4B44156364F99F8C6369DECB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he later (
<bibRefCitation id="165D1195FED40EC9A86ABCD824591E0D" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B64" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1941. A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania. University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series 14: 1 - 161" title="A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania." volume="14" year="1941">Wehmeyer 1941</bibRefCitation>
) argued that the conidia only differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="19CED29314B6540C735F9783423E19DC" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="D82631C8F5275C77A177E9E6B4B93B7E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in depth of pigmentation and, therefore, reduced 
<taxonomicName id="E3E733C08D92A5C316B1FE4241B8EE36" genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="9C8FFE9A290B5A7680FE56940E2AD805" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to a subspecies of the latter. In Europe, where, owing to 
<bibRefCitation id="3DA9885D7E4C3EA0E4AAFC4B216D5988" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B64" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1941. A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania. University of Michigan Studies, Scientific Series 14: 1 - 161" title="A Revision of Melanconis, Pseudovalsa, Prosthecium, and Titania." volume="14" year="1941">Wehmeyer (1941)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F1A36A665F70EC6B3401CA5621A33F8A" authorityName="Tul. &amp; C. Tul., Select. fung. carpol. (Paris) 2: 115" authorityYear="1863" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="673F8DBEB1AFBA5C19D972B66CD4A2BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="13D6773E7F6BD7E789D46293C53AACE2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Alnus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="02C60C621A7AFA677F518D99FD430C94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Alnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was always identified as 
<taxonomicName id="AB09F263F9D6789B80704106F64FB4FD" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="417DFD1070B5397E106223E2BA2789D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B650FAFC74BA3C996DDB4D30A126F6C5" author="Petrak, F" journalOrPublisher="Annales Mycologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="251 - 349" refId="B32" refString="Petrak, F, 1941. Mykologische Notizen. Annales Mycologici 39: 251 - 349" title="Mykologische Notizen." volume="39" year="1941">Petrak (1941)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="C70ABDA92DD841E385C957B78367D5A7" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium dimorphum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dimorphum">
<emphasis id="2D988DCCB7D3C8C8E5811D0135BBD4D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconium dimorphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time, described both conidial types, but still found it probable that 
<taxonomicName id="6A4D60AF752DE1113B055F45870B06C3" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconium dimorphum" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dimorphum">
<emphasis id="7AD04C05C09AFF8EDC4E80C640D8F861" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconium dimorphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was an abnormal form of 
<taxonomicName id="FBFC87837BECA6DF95BF3C1EC074F9E7" genus="M." lsidName="M. sphaeroideum" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="sphaeroideum">
<emphasis id="BE74CFBD6B8D4BF7B63D6A50F9C08724" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. sphaeroideum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the putative name of the asexual morph of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6919CA83EA089864A682D13224227C" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="A2E379347EC6C1D9ECABF93898F999C6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="1546DB849B9B5928B634AEA820185518" author="Kobayashi, T" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Government Forest Experimental Station Meguro" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 242" refId="B24" refString="Kobayashi, T, 1970. Taxonomic studies of Japanese Diaporthaceae with special reference to their life-histories. Bulletin of the Government Forest Experimental Station Meguro 226: 1 - 242" title="Taxonomic studies of Japanese Diaporthaceae with special reference to their life-histories." volume="226" year="1970">Kobayashi (1970)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="AAE7FF5D68BC22C6AEAD61FCF639469A" author="Jensen, JD" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" pagination="275 - 281" refId="B21" refString="Jensen, JD, 1984. Melanconis marginalis from Northern Idaho. Mycotaxon 20: 275 - 281" title="Melanconis marginalis from Northern Idaho." volume="20" year="1984">Jensen (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, however, were convinced that 
<taxonomicName id="DA557153496DB4613E9F17334F2FC4F6" authorityName="Wehm., Pap. Michigan Acad. I. 6: 382" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="Peck" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis marginalis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="FC860B026B502092FFBAF68A0E27324A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">Melanconis marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a species separate from 
<taxonomicName id="EC55E824A2EC2970B214F44CD84F4541" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="7E0A0BBBE2C47FBC68B7FA24EFE9660C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is here confirmed phylogenetically. In addition, ascospores of 
<taxonomicName id="550689624340667663D5E0E48296B8E0" genus="M." lsidName="M. marginalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis id="91B52D4D705807C887372056E8BA0057" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are narrower, usually more oblong and symmetric than those of 
<taxonomicName id="802DCA106BD53E48B504136D812E9E43" genus="M." lsidName="M. alni" pageId="0" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="alni">
<emphasis id="C0F21525AA22B636B09AD6BD7E8BDC25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69">M. alni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and appendages shorter, stouter and rounded or truncate at the ends, which swell and become diffuse in mounts.
</paragraph>
